  "notes": "Standard Uzbek in Latin script (official since 1993, Unicode apostrophe forms oʻ and gʻ). No vowel harmony (unlike most Turkic). 6-vowel system. Q is uvular /q/. Oʻ represents /ø/ (front rounded). Gʻ represents voiced uvular fricative /ʁ/.",
